<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08405</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : PHILIPPINE CROWDSOURCING ACT OF 2018</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to improve the process of charting policies that shall provide the country's desired direction through expanding the avenues of participation to the Filipino online community.

Intends to make good use of social media to give voice to the brilliant ideas and greatest concerns of the people through law-making, and make the Government to become much closer to the people it has sworn to serve so that democracy will flourish.

Refers "CROWDSOURCING" as a law that allows the public to participate in the legislative process wherever they are and it believes in the power of online crowdsourcing.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-10-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Robes (000 2019-02-04)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Under deliberation by the Mother Committee on 2019-01-30</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Recommendations submitted by the TWG on 2019-02-07</b><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB09212</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PEOPLE'S PARTICIPATION ON 2018-10-10</td></tr></table>